## DEC-003 — 2026-05-15 18:05 — Raw-mode rendering polish: codeFont sizing, gutter alignment, gutter scroll-sync
**Iteration:** 1
**Decision:** Three non-AC-load-bearing implementation choices made during iteration-1 hand-testing: (a) `codeFont` is bumped from 13.5pt to 14pt monospaced to match `rawBody` so code-block lines and surrounding raw text share the same line height; (b) the `LineNumberRulerView` no longer adds both `textContainerOrigin.y` and `textContainerInset.height` — these were double-counting the same vertical offset, shifting gutter numbers downward by `verticalPadding` (32pt); (c) the gutter ruler now observes `NSView.boundsDidChangeNotification` on the scroll view's `contentView` so it redraws on every scroll tick (with `allowsNonContiguousLayout = true`, the layout manager can return stale fragment rects mid-scroll).
**Rationale:** All three are bug fixes for raw-mode gutter rendering. None of AC11.1–AC11.3 (or any other AC) pinned these specific numbers/mechanisms; the choices live in the implementation layer.
**Related:** AC11.1, AC11.2, AC11.3, AC14.4
**Context:** Auto-logged during /spec reconcile (iteration 1); bucket-1 (decision-only) drift items B, C, D.

